JOHANNESBURG - Stormy weather has made headlines since last week after a flash flood brought more than 90mm of rain in under an hour for parts of Johannesburg while bringing much needed rainfall for the eastern parts of South Africa. While Sunday was a clear day, more thunderstorms are expected over the north-eastern parts of the country Monday and Tuesday. See our full forecast for the week A ridging high causing an onshore flow of cool air will keep it cool and mostly cloudy for the coastal areas with some light rain possible.  On Tuesday the ridge strengthens pushing in more cool air for eastern South Africa where much cooler daytime temperatures are expected. Due to unstable conditions isolated rain and thundershowers are also in the forecast.   eNCA